# case study of Empower Finances

## Overview and Origin

* Empower

* When was the company incorporated? 03/18/2016

* Who are the founders of the company?
The founders of the company are, Jeffery Hall Brock and Warren Hogart

* How did the idea for the company (or project) come about? Personalized financial assistance, the company uses the phrase “helping people achieve financial freedom”.

* How is the company funded? How much funding have they received?
They are funded by investors such as Sequoia Capital, Paycheck Protection Program, and Initialized Capital.


## Business Activities:

* What specific financial problem is the company or project trying to solve? This company aims to make investing easy to do and understand. 
It shows people where they are and how to get to where they want to be.

* Who is the company's intended customer?  Is there any information about the market size of this set of customers?
Their target market is people who are middle aged and well off with a solid collection of assets.

*What solution does this company offer that their competitors do not or cannot offer? (What is the unfair advantage they utilize?) 
They use robo advisors to analyze the clients current path and what changes or adaptations need to be made in order to get the most from their assets. An advantage they have is their extremely user friendly set up that makes everything very clear, and they also have live financial advisors. Users have access to any tool necessary to see how things are going.

* Which technologies are they currently using, and how are they implementing them? (This may take a little bit of sleuthing–– you may want to search the company’s engineering blog or use sites like Stackshare to find this information.)
They use algorithms to see where the client is and is heading, they have an easy to use platform. They use asset location technologies that put your assets into tax efficient accounts and harvest tax loss from them. They also use robo advisors.


## Landscape:

* What domain of the financial industry is the company in? They are in asset management 

* What have been the major trends and innovations of this domain over the last 5-10 years. Some Innovations have been the rapid digital tools available for online banking and asset management. A negative trend is the decline of cyber security.
 
* What are the other major companies in this domain?
Reftab, Geowealth, and Black Rock are some of Empowers competitors.

## Results

* What has been the business impact of this company so far?
Empower retained  ~$174 billion in client assets they also kept 87 percent of all plans.


* What are some of the core metrics that companies in this domain use to measure success? How is your company performing, based on these metrics? They seem to be doing really well. The core metrics tend to be success rate, how much their customers profit along with easy of use.

* How is your company performing relative to competitors in the same domain? It is doing very well. They aren't JP Morgan by any means but they are doing good.


## Recommendations

* If you were to advise the company, what products or services would you suggest they offer? (This could be something that a competitor offers, or use your imagination!) I think they should offer investments that are local and would have a bigger impact on the community.

* Why do you think that offering this product or service would benefit the company?
I think that if their analysts are as good as they say, the investments would be solid and it would help a bigger group of people.
* What technologies would this additional product or service utilize?
Tracking businesses in the area, tracking consumer reports for that area, creating a database that learns from that.
* Why are these technologies appropriate for your solution?
Because investing without solid backing isn't what this company is about.
